***************************** PLOT ******************************
**                      XmGrace from command-line              **
**                      Adriano Amaricci 2012-13               **
*****************************************************************

[... |] xplot [options] [files]
Options:   -x<min:max>   x-interval    -x0:10
           -y<min:max>   y-interval    -y-2.5:0.75
           -lx           x log-scale 
           -ly           y log-scale 
           -lw           line width 
           -uX:Yn/F(Yn)  x,y  nth-columns -u1:3; -u1:2,1:3; -uall; -uone/-u1; -u1:'cos($2)'
           -m[w:h]       set fixed window format (default free)[wdith:height]
           -show         print cmd line on std.out
           -s<file>      save output to file.agr
           -t<string>    set title
           -xt<string>   set x-label
           -yt<string>   set y-label
           -l            legend on
           -d            legend on using directories
           -k            y-axis stride for data sets
           -w<l,p,lp>    set line type:line,points
           -c<C1:C2>     use a gradient between color C1 [black ]and color C2 [red];
           -h            this help

Examples:  plot data
           plot -u1:3 -x-1:1 data.1* -u1:2  data.0
           cat data | plot -uall
           seq -f%1.4f 0 0.01 6.28 |plot -u1:'cos($1)' -show
